Description: Small fragment of a seal-impression, the rear is smooth and rounded, maybe from a back of some sort. At the side impressions of a turned string. The fine brown Nile clay has inclusions of mica and was hardened after excavation. The front is rounded and shows finger prints as well as half a seal impression from a scarab-like seal. In the middle there is the cartouche Mn-khpr-R', surrounded by two elements that are barely recognisable, maybe falcons?
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E14.7 temple magazine
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
